org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.cloudlet

Class CloudletSchedulerDynamicWorkload

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.cloudlet.CloudletSchedulerAbstract
      • org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.cloudlet.CloudletSchedulerTimeShared
        • org.cloudbus.cloudsim.schedulers.cloudlet.CloudletSchedulerDynamicWorkload
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, CloudletScheduler

    public class CloudletSchedulerDynamicWorkload
extends CloudletSchedulerTimeShared
    CloudletSchedulerDynamicWorkload implements a policy of scheduling performed by a virtual machine to run its Cloudlets, assuming there is just one cloudlet which is working as an online service. It extends a TimeShared policy, but in fact, considering that there is just one cloudlet for the VM using this scheduler, the cloudlet will not compete for CPU with other ones. Each VM has to have its own instance of a CloudletScheduler.
    Since:
    CloudSim Toolkit 2.0
    Author:
    Anton Beloglazov

      • getTotalCurrentAvailableMipsForCloudlet

        public double getTotalCurrentAvailableMipsForCloudlet(CloudletExecutionInfo rcl,
                                                      List<Double> mipsShare)
        Description copied from class: CloudletSchedulerTimeShared
        Gets the total current mips that a Cloudlet can use for each PE it requires. Thus, the value returned by the method indicates the amount of MIPS each Cloudlet PE can use. It in fact doesn't consider the parameters given because in the Time Shared Scheduler, the CPU capacity from the VM that is managed by the scheduler is shared between all running cloudlets.
        Specified by:
        getTotalCurrentAvailableMipsForCloudlet in interface CloudletScheduler
        Overrides:
        getTotalCurrentAvailableMipsForCloudlet in class CloudletSchedulerTimeShared
        Parameters:
        rcl - the rcl
        mipsShare - the mips share
        Returns:
        the total current mips available for each Cloudlet PE
